1) Open the cloned folder with vscode or any text editor
2)Create a developer account in twitter
4)Create an app and generate required tokens
3)Enable Filtered Stream for the created app from Option(Labs>Manage )
5)In the config.js file fill the required feilds with tokens generated from twitter developer account
6)Open terminal in the cloned folder and run "npm install" to install dependencies
7)after installing all dependencies run "node server.js" this will start the server at port 8080
8)open another terminal in the same folder and run "npm start" this will start react application in port 3000 
9) By default the app is hardcoded to get tweets on (java,javascript,firebase)
10)search using a keyword to get custom tweets
